activities.message:
Alright, enjoy your vacation and thanks for the heads up !

I've thought about fixes for this, but I have a few questions to not interfere with "design" and functionality.
What I can say though is the core issue of this problem, is the fact that a file is checked using a function that references it by a path (stat) and than is later opened with the same path.
To fix the core of this vulnerability we'd want to use a function such as fstat instead so that checks can be done on a fd instead of by file name.

My question would be, what exactly is the purpose of this code ? As in, what were the intended types of files that should be opened by fopen in this case by design ? 
```
  if(stat(filename, &sb) == -1 || !S_ISREG(sb.st_mode)) {
    /* a non-regular file, fallback to direct fopen() */
    *fh = fopen(filename, FOPEN_WRITETEXT);
    if(*fh)
      return CURLE_OK;
    goto fail;
  }
```
And was is intended that for a symlink pointing to a regular file: !S_ISREG(sb.st_mode)) == false  ?

Don't feel pressured to answer this message, enjoy your vacation. 
I will think about it more and read curl's doc more in depth to make sure I don't disregard some functionalities. And I'll come back with hopefully good fixes for this issue, so that we can eliminate the issue at its core.

So my idea to keep it as close to how it is currently, would be something like this :

Current version
```
...
	if(stat(filename, &sb) == -1 || !S_ISREG(sb.st_mode)) {
	/* a non-regular file, fallback to direct fopen() */
		*fh = fopen(filename, FOPEN_WRITETEXT);
		if(*fh)
			return CURLE_OK;
		goto fail;
  }
...
``` 
Fix version
```
...
	*fh = fopen(filename, FOPEN_WRITETEXT);
	if (!*fh)
		goto fail;
	if (fstat(fileno(*fh), &sb) == -1 || !S_ISREG(sb.st_mode))
		return CURLE_OK;
	fclose(*fh);
	*fh = NULL;
...

```

What do you think of this ?

Proper patch file in case this is approved.
```
diff --git a/lib/fopen.c b/lib/fopen.c
index c9c9e3d6e..cb9e48ba9 100644
--- a/lib/fopen.c
+++ b/lib/fopen.c
@@ -56,14 +56,13 @@ CURLcode Curl_fopen(struct Curl_easy *data, const char *filename,
   int fd = -1;
   *tempname = NULL;

-  if(stat(filename, &sb) == -1 || !S_ISREG(sb.st_mode)) {
-    /* a non-regular file, fallback to direct fopen() */
-    *fh = fopen(filename, FOPEN_WRITETEXT);
-    if(*fh)
-      return CURLE_OK;
+  *fh = fopen(filename, FOPEN_WRITETEXT);
+  if (!*fh)
     goto fail;
-  }
-
+  if (fstat(fileno(*fh), &sb) == -1 || !S_ISREG(sb.st_mode))
+    return CURLE_OK;
+  fclose(*fh);
+  *fh = NULL;
   result = Curl_rand_hex(data, randsuffix, sizeof(randsuffix));
   if(result)
     goto fail;
```

